(
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAFFFBCC6AC576EFEA3F9D7" box="[159,302,1629,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">Figs. 20A–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAFFFBCC70B576EFE07F9D8" box="[312,394,1629,1656]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">26C–D</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFAFFFBBC6A45796FE0FF81A" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="229" pageId="27" pageNumber="228" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAFFFBCC6A45796FED6F8EF" blockId="27.[151,1437,1701,2016]" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAFFFBCC6A45796FE9FF91F" bold="true" box="[151,274,1701,1727]" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Apical seta longer than maximum width of palpus; tarsomere 5 shorter than tarsomere 1; setal palisade 2/3 length of mid tibia; setulae below basal half of hind femur shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half; tergite VI reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 2 long and 2 short setulae in transverse row; sternite VI divided into two boot-shaped plate; dorsum of oviscape with about 3–4 minute setulae each side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFAFFFBBC6F4566AFE2DFF75" blockId="27.[151,1437,1701,2016]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="229" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFAFFFBCC6F4566AFEA8F8D3" bold="true" box="[199,293,1881,1907]" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFAFFFBCC7F1566AFDE7F8D4" box="[450,618,1881,1908]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.26" metricValueMin="1.24" pageId="27" pageNumber="228" unit="mm" value="1.25" valueMax="1.26" valueMin="1.24">1.24–1.26 mm</quantity>
. Frons (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFAFFFBCC4F4566AFCA2F8D3" box="[711,815,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="228">Fig. 20A</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown, with 28–30 setulae. Supra-antennal setae as strong as adjacent frontal setae, upper pair being higher on frons than lower fronto-orbital setae. Lower interfrontal seta directly under lower fronto-orbital seta. Second row of frontal setae clearly concave, with upper interfronal setae further from each other than either is from upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 yellow and subglobose. Palpus pale yellow, with 6 long setae, apical seta a little longer than maximum width of palpus. Labrum and labella pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA8FFBBC6F451ECFB28FE0D" blockId="28.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">
Thorax yellowish brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior twice length of anterior. Legs yellow. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 0.90: 0.71: 0.61: 0.59: 1, with all five bearing a setal palisade (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC35C5030FF47FEE1" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). Setal palisade terminates 2/3 (0.65) length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC5705014FC26FEE1" box="[835,939,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
). Setae below basal half of hind femur a little shorter than those of anteroventral row of outer half (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC4DC5078FCDBFEC5" box="[751,854,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC5865078FB97FEC5" box="[949,1050,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 20B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA8FFBBC2445079FB53FEC5" box="[1143,1246,330,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="1.35">1.35 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA8FFBBC3025078FA15FEC5" box="[1329,1432,331,357]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8999999999999995" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="0.69">0.69 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.51. Costal index 0.40. Costal ratios 1.42:1. Costal cilia 
<quantity id="4CE38B8CFFA8FFBBC59D505DFBE3FE29" box="[942,1134,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5500000000000003" metricValueMax="3.5999999999999996" metricValueMin="3.5000000000000004" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" unit="mm" value="0.0355" valueMax="0.036" valueMin="0.035">
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFA8FFBBC59D505DFC61FE29" box="[942,1004,366,393]" degrees="0.035" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" precision="55" value="0.035">0.035</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE2F40AEFFA8FFBBC5DE505DFBB7FE29" box="[1005,1082,366,393]" degrees="0.036" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" precision="55" value="-0.036">–0.036</geoCoordinate>
mm
</quantity>
long. Costa with 16 dorsal setulae. Alula with 3 setae. Veins slightly yellow, membrane hyaline. Haltere whitish yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6476E1FFA8FFBBC6A457B1FAEFF91E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" startId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" targetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA8FFBBC6A457B1FAEFF91E" blockId="28.[151,1436,1666,1726]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA8FFBBC6A457B1FED6F93A" bold="true" box="[151,347,1666,1690]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">FIGURES 20A–F.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA8FFBBC75157B1FDF1F93A" authority="Liu &amp; Disney, 2022" authorityName="Liu &amp; Disney" authorityYear="2022" box="[354,636,1666,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calceoliformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA8FFBBC75157B1FDF1F93A" box="[354,636,1666,1690]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Pseudacteon calceoliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA8FFBBC4B757B1FD58F93A" bold="true" box="[644,725,1666,1690]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C4700FFA8FFBBC4B757B1FD58F93A" box="[644,725,1666,1690]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA8FFBBC6F457DFFB9DF837" blockId="28.[151,1436,1772,2015]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">
Abdominal tergites yellowish brown and tergites I–V with sparse minute setulae on posterior margins. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC6F65623FEA7F88B" box="[197,298,1808,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 26C</figureCitation>
) reduced to a narrow anterior strip in middle but each lateral quarter bears 2 long and 2 short setulae in transverse row. Venter pale yellow. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC4E65607FCB0F8EF" box="[725,829,1844,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 26" captionStartId="35.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[220,1379,181,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-19@35.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURES 26A–J. Tergite VI and sternite VI of females.A–B. P. yunnanensis sp. nov.; C–D. P. calceoliformis sp. nov.; E–F. P. hexasetalis Liu et Wang; G–H. P. tianmuensis sp. nov.; I–J. P. parviflavus sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559619" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559619/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 26D</figureCitation>
) long and wide, concaved in middle and with a bootshaped plate each side, with 2 short setulae at posterior margin. The dorsum of the oviscape with about 3–4 minute setulae each side. The venter of the oviscape without minute setulae (
<figureCitation id="13203AECFFA8FFBBC5AC564FFB8EF837" box="[927,1027,1916,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 20" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1666,1690]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetId="figure-156@28.[151,1435,450,1639]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 20A–F. Pseudacteon calceoliformis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. fore tarsus, posterior view; D. mid tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. ovipositor, ventral view. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6559601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6559601/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Fig. 20F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA8FFBBC6F45692FE0FF81A" blockId="28.[151,1436,1772,2015]" box="[199,386,1952,1979]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA8FFBBC6F45692FE86F81B" bold="true" box="[199,267,1953,1979]" pageId="28" pageNumber="229">Male.</emphasis>
