<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFA9FFBAC6F45031FE53FEC5" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFA9FFBAC6F45031FE53FEC5" blockId="29.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC6F45031FEB6FEBC" bold="true" box="[199,315,258,284]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is easily distinguished from other species of the genus by its boot-shaped sternite VI. It is a little similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFA9FFBAC7BB5014FD77FEE0" authority="Liu et Wang, 2013" authorityName="Liu et Wang" authorityYear="2013" box="[392,762,294,321]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hexasetalis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC7BB5014FDADFEE0" box="[392,544,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">P. hexasetalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFA9FFBAC4145015FD77FEE0" author="Liu, G. C. &amp; Wang, J. F. &amp; Cai, Y. L." box="[551,762,294,321]" pageId="29" pageNumber="230" pagination="53 - 58" refId="ref22208" refString="Liu, G. C., Wang, J. F. &amp; Cai, Y. L. (2013) The ant-parasitizing genus Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from China with description of three new species. Entomologica Fennica, 24, 53 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.33338 / ef. 7867" type="journal article" year="2013">
Liu 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFA9FFBAC4665014FDE4FEE0" box="[597,617,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="230">et</emphasis>
Wang, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter by boot-shaped sternite VI and two pairs of supra-antennal setae.
</paragraph>
